text
@a90 11
<p>
<dt>
<tt><strong>pki</strong> <em>hostname</em> <strong>dhparams</strong> <em>dhfile</em></tt>
<dd>
Associate the Diffie-Hellman parameters located in <tt><em>dhfile</em></tt>
with <tt><em>hostname</em></tt>.
The parameters are used for ephemeral key exchange.
If not specified, <a href="http://man.openbsd.org/smtpd">smtpd(8)</a>
will use safely generated built-in parameters.
Creation of Diffie-Hellman parameters is documented in
<a href="http://man.openbsd.org/openssl">openssl(1)</a>.
